00:15:28,635 --> 00:15:31,900
Listen. A friend of mine is having
a barbecue for her husband on Saturday,

248
00:15:31,935 --> 00:15:33,500
and I think you should come.

249
00:15:33,535 --> 00:15:36,100
Really?
- Yes, and bring Ginger.

250
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:39,300
Ginger? I don't know if she can make it.

251
00:15:39,335 --> 00:15:44,000
But you have to bring Ginger, because
if Rex sees you two together, he'll relax.

252
00:15:44,035 --> 00:15:46,500
Oh. Uh--

253
00:15:46,535 --> 00:15:47,500
OK.

254
00:15:47,535 --> 00:15:50,415
Son of a bitch!

255
00:15:54,035 --> 00:15:56,600
You are out of toilet paper.

256
00:15:56,635 --> 00:16:00,595
Bree, I'll call you later!

257
00:16:04,435 --> 00:16:06,414
Lynette?

258
00:16:08,235 --> 00:16:11,400
Honey?
Are you home?

259
00:16:11,435 --> 00:16:13,700
Three months?

260
00:16:13,735 --> 00:16:17,200
God, you scared the hell out of me!

261
00:16:17,235 --> 00:16:19,900
Were you ever going to tell me?

262
00:16:19,935 --> 00:16:23,000
I wanted to, but I kept putting it off.

263
00:16:23,035 --> 00:16:24,600
I knew how you'd react.

264
00:16:24,635 --> 00:16:28,400
Congratulations, you read me like a book.

265
00:16:28,435 --> 00:16:31,400
Why would you hire that woman?

266
00:16:31,435 --> 00:16:34,800
Technically, Peterson found her.
I just vouched for her.

267
00:16:34,835 --> 00:16:37,500
Tom!
- Come on honey, I'm just helping her out.

268
00:16:37,535 --> 00:16:38,500
It's the least I can do.

269
00:16:38,535 --> 00:16:44,400
She was devastated when I left her for you.
I felt bad.

270
00:16:44,435 --> 00:16:47,200
Do you still have feelings for her?

271
00:16:47,235 --> 00:16:49,200
All right, I'm not talking to you.

272
00:16:49,235 --> 00:16:53,200
You can tell me you still care about her.
Don't you? Just a teeny tiny little bit?

273
00:16:53,235 --> 00:16:57,100
I was just trying to be a good guy.
That's all.

274
00:16:57,135 --> 00:17:00,400
Well you can't work with her.
- What do you want me to do, quit?

275
00:17:00,435 --> 00:17:02,800
Talk to Peterson. Maybe you can get a transfer.

276
00:17:02,835 --> 00:17:05,700
Weren't you guys planning on
starting something up in Belize?

277
00:17:05,735 --> 00:17:08,100
Honey, you're crazy!

278
00:17:08,135 --> 00:17:09,600
No, I'm serious.

279
00:17:09,635 --> 00:17:12,800
If she stays, I will haunt your office.

280
00:17:12,835 --> 00:17:15,100
I'll bring you lunch every day.

281
00:17:15,135 --> 00:17:18,700
I'll bring your kids to visit.
I will change diapers on your desk.

282
00:17:18,735 --> 00:17:22,100
Every birthday cake in the break room,
every retirement party,

283
00:17:22,135 --> 00:17:25,800
I will be there. Watching her.

284
00:17:25,835 --> 00:17:31,650
Well, I better get you a parking space.
Cause she's staying.

285
00:17:42,335 --> 00:17:45,309
Don't you think it spices up the room?

286
00:17:52,035 --> 00:17:58,956
Oh, I was just letting you a gift.
To apologize for throwing gravel in your face.

287
00:17:59,635 --> 00:18:01,500
You didn't have to do that.

288
00:18:01,535 --> 00:18:04,900
I kind of did.
I want us to be friends.

289
00:18:04,935 --> 00:18:09,500
Yeah, well--
that's not going to happen.

290
00:18:09,535 --> 00:18:11,100
Why not?

291
00:18:11,135 --> 00:18:14,700
Aside from you blinding me,

292
00:18:14,735 --> 00:18:17,500
several weeks ago 
you freaked out in my house.

293
00:18:17,535 --> 00:18:21,700
You screamed,
you threw furniture around--

294
00:18:21,735 --> 00:18:27,100
OK. I realize I was at a run that night.
But I was upset.

295
00:18:27,135 --> 00:18:30,300
You have to get over that.
For Julie's sake.

296
00:18:30,335 --> 00:18:31,300
For Julie's sake?

297
00:18:31,335 --> 00:18:32,500
How do you think it makes her feel

298
00:18:32,535 --> 00:18:35,200
that her mother and her boyfriend
can't even get along?

299
00:18:35,235 --> 00:18:41,100
Zach, Julie does not think of you 
as her boyfriend.

300
00:18:41,135 --> 00:18:45,100
In fact, I don't think 
she wants anything to do with you.

301
00:18:45,135 --> 00:18:46,700
She said that?

302
00:18:46,735 --> 00:18:47,600
Yeah.

303
00:18:47,635 --> 00:18:48,500
I don't believe you.

304
00:18:48,535 --> 00:18:51,100
Believe whatever you want.

305
00:18:51,135 --> 00:18:54,000
If she did, it's because
you told her stuff about me that's not true!

306
00:18:54,035 --> 00:18:57,100
Zach! Come here!

307
00:18:57,135 --> 00:18:58,602
Right now!

308
00:19:03,735 --> 00:19:08,190
Please. Don't ruin this for me.

309
00:19:30,235 --> 00:19:32,300
How do you know Mary Alice?

310
00:19:32,335 --> 00:19:33,100
Who?

311
00:19:33,135 --> 00:19:37,900
Mary Alice Young.
She lives next door to me in Fairview.

312
00:19:37,935 --> 00:19:40,600
She's standing right here in this picture with you.

313
00:19:40,635 --> 00:19:44,700
That's Angela Forrest. We worked together
at the rehab center, 15 years ago.

314
00:19:44,735 --> 00:19:48,573
Don't be dense, Felicia.
Don't you think I know my own neighbor?

315
00:19:50,935 --> 00:19:53,600
Does this Mary Alice have children?

316
00:19:53,635 --> 00:19:57,578
A teenager. Her boy.

317
00:19:59,935 --> 00:20:01,933
What?

318
00:20:02,835 --> 00:20:06,984
Angela and I worked together 
with a very disturbed young woman

319
00:20:07,019 --> 00:20:09,435
who gave birth to a baby boy.

320
00:20:09,435 --> 00:20:13,500
About a year later,
Angela and her husband

321
00:20:13,535 --> 00:20:15,000
disappeared.

322
00:20:15,035 --> 00:20:19,900
Not long after that,
I heard that the child was missing too.

323
00:20:19,935 --> 00:20:22,600
People said it was just a coincidence.

324
00:20:22,635 --> 00:20:28,600
But in my heart I always hoped
that she had given him a proper home.

325
00:20:28,635 --> 00:20:32,900
Are you saying
she stole the baby?

326
00:20:32,935 --> 00:20:38,400
Don't look shocked, Martha.
Makes your face look fat.

327
00:20:38,435 --> 00:20:42,500
The biological mother was a drug addict.

328
00:20:42,535 --> 00:20:46,100
If Angela really is your neighbor,
which I doubt,

329
00:20:46,135 --> 00:20:50,799
then that child was very lucky.

330
00:21:11,035 --> 00:21:12,800
Lynette, hey!

331
00:21:12,835 --> 00:21:14,400
If you're looking for Tom,
he's out with a client.

332
00:21:14,435 --> 00:21:17,800
No. I actually wanted to see you.

333
00:21:17,835 --> 00:21:20,300
That's really funny.
I was thinking the same thing.

334
00:21:20,335 --> 00:21:22,900
I've been here all this time.
We should go out.

335
00:21:22,935 --> 00:21:25,000
For lunch, just the two of us.

336
00:21:25,035 --> 00:21:27,800
Yeah, I'll check my book.

337
00:21:27,835 --> 00:21:30,400
So Annabelle--

338
00:21:30,435 --> 00:21:33,500
do you have feelings for Tom?

339
00:21:33,535 --> 00:21:34,700
What?

340
00:21:34,735 --> 00:21:36,100
You heard me.

341
00:21:36,135 --> 00:21:40,400
OK, you want to talk about this, Lynette?
Let's talk.

342
00:21:40,435 --> 00:21:44,500
Yes, Tom and I were in love.
But he married you.

343
00:21:44,535 --> 00:21:48,800
I'm not looking to break up a happy couple.

344
00:21:48,835 --> 00:21:52,400
Anyway, that's probably more <i>your</i> speed, isn't it?

345
00:21:52,435 --> 00:21:55,800
Morning, ladies.
Just gotten in for a little more fuel.

346
00:21:55,835 --> 00:22:00,300
Yeah, one man's sludge
is another man's liquid gold.

347
00:22:00,335 --> 00:22:03,589
Well, back to the trenches.

348
00:22:05,735 --> 00:22:08,300
Watch your step.
Tom and I are a team.

349
00:22:08,335 --> 00:22:12,500
Our marriage is rock solid.
Nothing you do could ever break that up.

350
00:22:12,535 --> 00:22:16,712
Then why are you down here right now,
warning me?

351
00:22:29,435 --> 00:22:34,400
Gabrielle! What brings you down here?

352
00:22:34,435 --> 00:22:38,400
Sweet mother of God,
what have you done this time?

353
00:22:38,435 --> 00:22:40,500
You're pregnant?
- Yes.

354
00:22:40,535 --> 00:22:43,000
And it's impossible, I'm on the pill!

355
00:22:43,035 --> 00:22:45,200
Which I know you probably think is a sin.
But it works.

356
00:22:45,235 --> 00:22:47,900
It's a 99.9% effective sin.

357
00:22:47,935 --> 00:22:51,000
Maybe it's in that 1/10 of a percent
that God resides.

358
00:22:51,035 --> 00:22:53,900
Couldn't wait to throw that in, could you?

359
00:22:53,935 --> 00:22:55,200
God is screwing with me.

360
00:22:55,235 --> 00:22:58,600
He doesn't like how I live my life,
so he's punishing me.

361
00:22:58,635 --> 00:23:02,565
Have you done something
that would warrant being punished?

362
00:23:03,835 --> 00:23:05,483
The gardener?

363
00:23:06,535 --> 00:23:07,800
I thought that was over.

364
00:23:07,835 --> 00:23:11,800
No, it was, and then--
He just happened to be there.

365
00:23:11,835 --> 00:23:14,400
That's my point:
I'd be an awful mother.

366
00:23:14,435 --> 00:23:19,000
I'm selfish, I'm self-centered--
The only person more self-centered than me is Carlos.

367
00:23:19,035 --> 00:23:22,400
He's so self-centered that he doesn't even know
how self-centered I am.

368
00:23:22,435 --> 00:23:23,700
We'd be terrible parents.

369
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:27,800
Gabrielle, I'd like to help.
But I'm not sure what it is you want.

370
00:23:27,835 --> 00:23:31,100
I want to know who to be angry at.

371
00:23:31,135 --> 00:23:35,000
Here's a thought:
Don't be angry. Be thankful.

372
00:23:35,035 --> 00:23:37,396
Children are a gift, are they not?

373
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:44,654
I don't have time for this crap.
I have a party to plan.

374
00:23:45,735 --> 00:23:49,500
Thanks.- Edie.
- Hi.

375
00:23:49,535 --> 00:23:50,800
Wow, things are really coming along.

376
00:23:50,835 --> 00:23:53,000
Yeah, slowly and expensively.

377
00:23:53,035 --> 00:23:56,331
It'll be worth it.
You're doing an amazing job.

378
00:23:57,835 --> 00:24:03,118
So, look, you're basically a-- predator,
and I need some advice.

379
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:09,500
... and I know Tom loves me,
but I don't trust this woman.

380
00:24:09,535 --> 00:24:11,800
I think there's an agenda there.

381
00:24:11,835 --> 00:24:14,300
I don't know. I bet I'm being paranoid.

382
00:24:14,335 --> 00:24:17,500
No, you did the right thing coming to me.

383
00:24:17,535 --> 00:24:20,300
There are two ways to approach this.

384
00:24:20,335 --> 00:24:23,200
But first I have to ask:
What kind of shape is this woman in?

385
00:24:23,235 --> 00:24:25,600
Fantastic shape. She's gorgeous.

386
00:24:25,635 --> 00:24:29,100
OK. Now there's only one way to approach this.

387
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:30,900
You're gonna have to act fast.

388
00:24:30,935 --> 00:24:31,700
I'm listening.

389
00:24:31,735 --> 00:24:35,300
It's really pretty simple.
When I feel threatened by a woman,

390
00:24:35,335 --> 00:24:38,500
I pull her in.
I make her my best friend.

391
00:24:38,535 --> 00:24:41,000
I thought you said
you didn't have any female friends.

392
00:24:41,035 --> 00:24:42,500
I don't.

393
00:24:42,535 --> 00:24:45,500
And I've never felt threatened by a woman either.

394
00:24:45,535 --> 00:24:47,700
But the point is:

395
00:24:47,735 --> 00:24:49,100
Keep your friends close,...

396
00:24:49,135 --> 00:24:53,106
... keep your enemies closer.

397
00:24:57,835 --> 00:25:03,286
Tom, we're having a dinner party.
I'm thinking of inviting Annabelle.

398
00:25:06,035 --> 00:25:08,800
We're not moving.
- Susan knows something.

399
00:25:08,835 --> 00:25:10,900
Edie said she--
- I don't care what Edie Britt said!

400
00:25:10,935 --> 00:25:12,100
I'm not leaving Julie!

401
00:25:12,135 --> 00:25:16,300
You want to risk our lives, our future
over some schoolyard crush?

402
00:25:16,335 --> 00:25:19,400
It's more than that.
Julie loves me.

403
00:25:19,435 --> 00:25:22,000
Then why does she refuse to see you?

404
00:25:22,035 --> 00:25:25,500
Mrs Mayer lies to her.
If it wasn't for that, she would be with me.

405
00:25:25,535 --> 00:25:27,258
Are you sure?

406
00:25:28,035 --> 00:25:30,500
You know, Julie is a-- very special girl.

407
00:25:30,535 --> 00:25:30,800
I know.

408
00:25:30,835 --> 00:25:34,826
She could have just about any boy she wanted.

409
00:25:35,535 --> 00:25:39,700
I think you're a wonderful kid.
I do, but--

410
00:25:39,735 --> 00:25:43,800
you're not that special, Zach.

411
00:25:43,835 --> 00:25:46,447
Not really.

412
00:25:46,535 --> 00:25:47,978
She kissed me.

413
00:25:48,535 --> 00:25:50,045
Lately?

414
00:25:52,335 --> 00:25:54,200
Let's pack our bags and get out of here.

415
00:25:54,235 --> 00:25:56,800
We can leave this whole mess behind,
start over.

416
00:25:56,835 --> 00:25:59,700
And there will be other girls,
I promise.

417
00:25:59,735 --> 00:26:01,400
No!

418
00:26:01,435 --> 00:26:03,500
If Susan goes to the police, it's over.

419
00:26:03,535 --> 00:26:06,500
They'll take me away.
They'll take you away. Don't you get that?

420
00:26:06,535 --> 00:26:09,600
If Julie doesn't love me anymore,
then it doesn't matter.

421
00:26:09,635 --> 00:26:11,891
None of it matters.

422
00:26:19,635 --> 00:26:22,500
Magruder had absolutely no idea 
what was going on.

423
00:26:22,535 --> 00:26:26,900
During the entire campaign,
he was practically holding Benson's hand!

424
00:26:26,935 --> 00:26:31,100
After the way they burned them, screwed them over! 
That was too...

425
00:26:31,135 --> 00:26:36,000
It was awful!

426
00:26:36,035 --> 00:26:38,900
Excuse me, I need to get in here
so I can clear the plates.

427
00:26:38,935 --> 00:26:42,300
You want some help with that?

428
00:26:42,335 --> 00:26:43,700
Looks like we got company.

429
00:26:43,735 --> 00:26:45,600
Hey guys, isn't it time for bed?

430
00:26:45,635 --> 00:26:49,000
Oh, they never get to see you.
Let them stay up for a while.

431
00:26:49,035 --> 00:26:52,597
OK, come here!
I want you to meet someone.

432
00:26:53,635 --> 00:26:56,000
This is Miss Foster.

433
00:26:56,035 --> 00:26:56,800
Hi.

434
00:26:56,835 --> 00:27:01,800
She's an old, <i>old</i> friend of your daddy's.

435
00:27:01,835 --> 00:27:04,700
Hey, what you got there?
- It's a picture we painted.

436
00:27:04,735 --> 00:27:07,100
Let me have a look at that.

437
00:27:07,135 --> 00:27:10,700
It's all of us with Mommy and Daddy.
We're really happy.

438
00:27:10,735 --> 00:27:14,000
It's so adorable.
When did you do this?

439
00:27:14,035 --> 00:27:16,900
Today, Mom told us to.

440
00:27:16,935 --> 00:27:19,800
I just told them to paint something nice.
The sentiment's all theirs.

441
00:27:19,835 --> 00:27:23,500
But you told us to--
- Hold on, honey, grown-ups are talking.

442
00:27:23,535 --> 00:27:26,300
Well, this is really neat.

443
00:27:26,335 --> 00:27:29,800
How would you boys like to
paint my portrait one day?

444
00:27:29,835 --> 00:27:32,600
Sure, you're pretty.
- OK, great.

445
00:27:32,635 --> 00:27:34,900
Like your dad said, it's time for bed.

446
00:27:34,935 --> 00:27:37,300
I'll take them back upstairs.

447
00:27:37,335 --> 00:27:39,200
Come on, guys!

448
00:27:39,235 --> 00:27:41,359
Thank you.

449
00:27:47,135 --> 00:27:48,400
I must say, Lynette.

450
00:27:48,435 --> 00:27:52,600
Your home is warm and inviting,
your children are absolutely precious--

451
00:27:52,635 --> 00:27:56,600
this whole evening was practically
a commercial for the perfect family.

452
00:27:56,635 --> 00:27:59,200
You think?

453
00:27:59,235 --> 00:28:04,400
You couldn't have planned it any better.
And I mean that.

454
00:28:04,435 --> 00:28:07,414
Good.

455
00:28:12,135 --> 00:28:14,500
Hello, Susan.

456
00:28:14,535 --> 00:28:17,500
Oh. Hi.

457
00:28:17,535 --> 00:28:21,900
I understand you and Edie went
snooping through my house.

458
00:28:21,935 --> 00:28:22,800
Huh?

459
00:28:22,835 --> 00:28:25,300
It's OK. I'm not mad.

460
00:28:25,335 --> 00:28:29,034
So, what do you want to know about Angela?

461
00:28:31,435 --> 00:28:35,900
It was Mary Alice's birth name.
She was named after her aunt Angela.

462
00:28:35,935 --> 00:28:40,000
When she was a teenager there were falling-outs.
So she changed her name into Mary Alice.

463
00:28:40,035 --> 00:28:45,246
This is before we were married,
so you'll forgive me if I'm hazy on the details.

464
00:28:45,535 --> 00:28:48,600
That's it?
That's the explanation?

465
00:28:48,635 --> 00:28:52,235
Ridiculously simple, isn't it?

466
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:57,200
She changed her name because
she got in a fight with her aunt?

467
00:28:57,235 --> 00:28:59,700
That doesn't seem like something
Mary Alice would do.

468
00:28:59,735 --> 00:29:05,300
Neither did suicide,
but we both know that she did it.

469
00:29:05,335 --> 00:29:09,200
So can we finally put this behind us?

470
00:29:09,235 --> 00:29:11,429
Or do you need to break into my home
for anything else?

471
00:29:12,908 --> 00:29:14,535
Uh--

472
00:29:16,235 --> 00:29:21,575
No.
I'm good. Thanks.

473
00:29:23,835 --> 00:29:24,900
Although--

474
00:29:24,935 --> 00:29:28,700
if you wouldn't mind,
I'd rather like to see that videotape I found.

475
00:29:28,735 --> 00:29:30,300
The one marked "Angela."

476
00:29:31,635 --> 00:29:34,259
Would be nice to see Mary Alice
when she was young.

477
00:29:35,135 --> 00:29:39,055
I'm afraid that box of tapes
was thrown out with the trash.

478
00:29:41,535 --> 00:29:43,196
OK then.

479
00:29:43,435 --> 00:29:45,600
Susan--

480
00:29:45,635 --> 00:29:49,000
I'm serious when I say
I hope you'll leave my family alone now.

481
00:29:49,035 --> 00:29:53,800
This endless suspicion of yours
has become very tiring.

482
00:29:53,835 --> 00:29:56,615
I couldn't agree more.

483
00:30:09,635 --> 00:30:13,591
Oh. That's my cell, sorry.

484
00:30:17,335 --> 00:30:21,700
Oh God, it's Peterson. Excuse me.
- Peterson?

485
00:30:21,735 --> 00:30:23,601
Hello? Yeah.

486
00:30:26,935 --> 00:30:29,615
That was quite a show you put on tonight.

487
00:30:30,535 --> 00:30:31,668
Show?

488
00:30:32,935 --> 00:30:36,500
The boys' paintings,
all those references to how happy we are--

489
00:30:36,535 --> 00:30:38,900
What's wrong with subtly reminding Annabelle
that you're happily married?

490
00:30:38,935 --> 00:30:41,654
Because it wasn't subtle.

491
00:30:41,835 --> 00:30:44,090
And it's an insult to me.

492
00:30:45,335 --> 00:30:48,295
I did not mean it that way.

493
00:30:50,635 --> 00:30:53,600
Are you so insecure that you
have to pull that crap?

494
00:30:53,635 --> 00:30:56,669
Keep your voice down!

495
00:30:56,835 --> 00:31:00,800
It doesn't matter if she has feelings for me
as long as I'm not interested.

496
00:31:00,835 --> 00:31:03,700
Have I ever, ever
given you any reason to doubt me?

497
00:31:03,735 --> 00:31:08,400
Anyone is capable of anything.
The first time we ever met, you were cheating.

498
00:31:08,435 --> 00:31:10,500
With you! Cheating with you!

499
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:11,900
It's a pattern of behavior.

500
00:31:11,935 --> 00:31:13,800
Uh, give me a break!

501
00:31:13,835 --> 00:31:15,500
What am I supposed to do?

502
00:31:15,535 --> 00:31:19,400
You hire your old girlfriend and
you don't tell me about it for 3 months?

503
00:31:19,435 --> 00:31:22,500
I could've told you from Day One
and you'd still be jumping at my throat.

504
00:31:22,535 --> 00:31:24,900
Annabelle is ancient history.

505
00:31:24,935 --> 00:31:26,200
She's in the next room.

506
00:31:26,235 --> 00:31:30,500
How long do we have to be married, Lynette,
until you actually trust me?

507
00:31:30,535 --> 00:31:31,700
I trust you.

508
00:31:31,735 --> 00:31:33,600
How many times have you said to me:
"If you ever touch another woman,

509
00:31:33,635 --> 00:31:37,500
"I'll take the boys and walk out of here
and you'll never see us again!"

510
00:31:37,535 --> 00:31:40,600
That's just something
wives say to their husbands.

511
00:31:40,635 --> 00:31:43,700
Not all wives.

512
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:47,200
You're so convinced that I'll be unfaithful!

513
00:31:47,235 --> 00:31:51,100
It makes me sick!
The distrust, the paranoia,--

514
00:31:51,135 --> 00:31:58,100
It seems like you won't be happy until you
drive me out of this marriage to prove yourself right!

515
00:31:58,135 --> 00:32:01,600
Wait. Forget I said that.

516
00:32:01,635 --> 00:32:05,221
It's too late.
You said it.

517
00:32:05,535 --> 00:32:10,379
Well, then just consider it something
husbands say to their wives.

518
00:32:11,635 --> 00:32:17,200
Peterson's on cloud nine.
He discovered some inside scoop on the Metro account.

519
00:32:17,235 --> 00:32:20,700
The bad news is,
we'll have to redo the entire presentation.

520
00:32:20,735 --> 00:32:21,700
Tonight?

521
00:32:21,735 --> 00:32:23,000
He'll need it first thing in the morning.

522
00:32:23,035 --> 00:32:26,500
Peterson says we might be pulling an all-nighter.

523
00:32:26,535 --> 00:32:28,500
I can't drive. I've been drinking.

524
00:32:28,535 --> 00:32:31,600
I'll drive. Come on.
- Thanks.

525
00:32:31,635 --> 00:32:35,692
Don't worry, Lynette.
I'll deliver him back to you as soon as I can.

526
00:32:36,835 --> 00:32:38,718
Please do.

527
00:32:52,635 --> 00:32:56,200
Honey, take over for a minute.
I'm giving a speech.

528
00:32:56,235 --> 00:32:58,518
Make sure they stay pink like that, OK?

529
00:32:59,435 --> 00:33:01,200
Are you OK?

530
00:33:01,235 --> 00:33:09,500
Oh. I just--
realize how disgusting meat can be.

531
00:33:09,535 --> 00:33:13,600
Everyone, I just want to say
it means a lot to me that you all came,

532
00:33:13,635 --> 00:33:18,600
and as you know, in a few days
I'll be taking a little government-sponsored vacation.

533
00:33:18,635 --> 00:33:22,324
Lucky for me, breakfast is included.

534
00:33:24,235 --> 00:33:25,000
Oh God.

535
00:33:25,035 --> 00:33:28,700
The bottom line is,
I'm going away to jail.

536
00:33:28,735 --> 00:33:33,900
And when a man has to go to jail,
which I hope none of you will ever have to do,

537
00:33:33,935 --> 00:33:36,300
he sees who his real friends are.

538
00:33:36,335 --> 00:33:38,850
So thanks.

539
00:33:39,135 --> 00:33:40,750
Cheers!

540
00:33:48,535 --> 00:33:50,987
Excuse you.

541
00:33:53,635 --> 00:33:57,800
Stay put until I need you.
Don't talk to anybody and, for God's sake,

542
00:33:57,835 --> 00:33:59,000
don't get drunk!

543
00:33:59,035 --> 00:34:00,900
You know I was supposed to
go to my cousin's wedding today.

544
00:34:00,935 --> 00:34:05,100
It's not a wedding, it's a commitment.
So sit down and

545
00:34:05,135 --> 00:34:07,862
try to fit in.

546
00:34:13,035 --> 00:34:16,143
Urghh.

547
00:34:27,435 --> 00:34:29,200
Got you a hot dog.

548
00:34:29,235 --> 00:34:30,700
No thanks. I'm full.

549
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:34,500
They have a croquet set.
You wanna go hit some balls?

550
00:34:34,535 --> 00:34:35,600
No.

551
00:34:35,635 --> 00:34:37,300
That's fine. We can just sit here.

552
00:34:37,335 --> 00:34:38,369
Zach!

553
00:34:39,535 --> 00:34:40,200
I don't want to be your girlfriend.

554
00:34:40,235 --> 00:34:46,600
I don't want to hang out with you.
I just want you to leave me alone, OK?

555
00:34:46,635 --> 00:34:48,235
OK--

556
00:35:28,535 --> 00:35:31,000
<i>In that moment,

557
00:35:31,035 --> 00:35:34,200
<i>while looking at the pills
that had been so obviously tampered with,

558
00:35:34,235 --> 00:35:40,300
<i>Gabrielle's nausea was suddenly replaced
by an even stronger sensation:

559
00:35:40,335 --> 00:35:41,952
<i>rage.

560
00:35:58,935 --> 00:36:00,356
What are you doing?

561
00:36:00,835 --> 00:36:03,400
I'm so sorry.
That was an accident.

562
00:36:03,435 --> 00:36:05,900
Answer my question:
What are you doing here?

563
00:36:05,935 --> 00:36:07,200
I was invited.

564
00:36:07,235 --> 00:36:10,000
By who?
- You know what, Dr Van de Kamp?

565
00:36:10,035 --> 00:36:12,600
I don't believe I have to answer to you.
- I think you do.

566
00:36:12,635 --> 00:36:13,700
What's going on here?

567
00:36:13,735 --> 00:36:17,600
He crashed the party.
This guy clearly is not taking "no" for an answer.

568
00:36:17,635 --> 00:36:20,900
It's OK. George has a girlfriend.

569
00:36:20,935 --> 00:36:22,000
You brought her, didn't you?

570
00:36:22,035 --> 00:36:24,700
He doesn't have a girlfriend.
- I do, sir.

571
00:36:24,735 --> 00:36:26,500
She's right over there.

572
00:36:30,235 --> 00:36:31,500
That's his girlfriend?

573
00:36:31,535 --> 00:36:35,100
See? You were worried for nothing.

574
00:36:35,135 --> 00:36:39,767
So, any time you want to apologize--

575
00:36:39,802 --> 00:36:44,575
Come on, Rex.
You owe George some sort of gesture.

576
00:36:49,935 --> 00:36:52,628
What the hell.

577
00:37:01,135 --> 00:37:03,200
Rex! Have you lost your mind?

578
00:37:03,235 --> 00:37:06,208
To be fair, I only pushed <i>him</i>.

579
00:37:07,435 --> 00:37:09,200
Carlos! You son of a bitch!

580
00:37:09,235 --> 00:37:12,457
I am pregnant and it's all your fault!

581
00:37:20,035 --> 00:37:20,900
Wow.

582
00:37:20,935 --> 00:37:24,340
This is turning into one hell of a party.

583
00:37:29,135 --> 00:37:31,200
Are you OK?

584
00:37:31,235 --> 00:37:35,000
I think I can honestly say:
No. I'm not.

585
00:37:35,035 --> 00:37:37,600
I'm so sorry.

586
00:37:37,635 --> 00:37:39,300
Thanks.

587
00:37:39,335 --> 00:37:42,600
But you know what they say about kids:

588
00:37:42,635 --> 00:37:45,300
that you can't imagine having them
until you do,

589
00:37:45,335 --> 00:37:48,900
and then you can't imagine
life without them?

590
00:37:48,935 --> 00:37:50,549
It's true.

591
00:37:54,035 --> 00:37:58,700
All I'm saying is,
maybe this is a blessing in disguise.

592
00:37:58,735 --> 00:38:01,400
I don't know who the father is.

593
00:38:01,435 --> 00:38:04,400
What?
- Yeah.

594
00:38:04,435 --> 00:38:07,300
So you mean you and John have still been...
- Yeah.

595
00:38:07,335 --> 00:38:08,500
Gabby!

596
00:38:08,535 --> 00:38:10,954
I know, Susan! I don't know what to do!

597
00:38:12,235 --> 00:38:14,300
Oh! Oh my God!

598
00:38:14,335 --> 00:38:15,600
That-- that's my house!

599
00:38:15,635 --> 00:38:21,566
Call 911?
- Yes, that's my house!

600
00:38:22,835 --> 00:38:27,845
Oh, look, my kitchen!
Oh, it's a big fire!

601
00:38:29,935 --> 00:38:33,900
Turns out someone left the gas on
with candles burning.

602
00:38:33,935 --> 00:38:38,300
That's impossible.
We don't burn candles during the day.

603
00:38:38,335 --> 00:38:43,900
Uh, well-- I-- did have
a French vanilla candle burning earlier, but--

604
00:38:43,935 --> 00:38:46,200
I'm almost positive I blew it out!

605
00:38:46,235 --> 00:38:48,115
You're <i>almost</i> positive?

606
00:38:50,235 --> 00:38:54,300
Yes! I did! I-- I think.

607
00:38:54,335 --> 00:38:59,100
You're lucky the fire was contained.
The damage could've been far more extensive.

608
00:38:59,135 --> 00:39:02,783
You've got to be more careful from now on.

609
00:39:09,235 --> 00:39:12,859
Don't worry. We will be.

610
00:39:17,935 --> 00:39:20,525
Bree, hi.
- Hi.

611
00:39:21,135 --> 00:39:22,100
You left the party so quickly,

612
00:39:22,135 --> 00:39:27,100
I didn't have a chance to apologize to you
for what Rex did.

613
00:39:27,135 --> 00:39:31,500
Oh George, I'm so sorry
he humiliated you in front of all these people.

614
00:39:31,535 --> 00:39:33,200
I don't know what got into him.

615
00:39:33,235 --> 00:39:35,700
Isn't it obvious?
He hates me.

616
00:39:35,735 --> 00:39:40,700
No, he doesn't hate you.
He really doesn't even know you, and you don't know him.

617
00:39:40,735 --> 00:39:44,434
I know this much:
he won't let us be friends.

618
00:39:45,635 --> 00:39:48,900
Well, that's not his choice to make.

619
00:39:48,935 --> 00:39:52,700
What if he asked you not to see me anymore?

620
00:39:52,735 --> 00:39:55,100
What if he orders you not to?

621
00:39:55,135 --> 00:39:56,500
Well--

622
00:39:56,535 --> 00:40:00,300
I decide who I need in my life,
and I've decided that I need you.

623
00:40:00,335 --> 00:40:03,500
That's all there is to it.

624
00:40:03,535 --> 00:40:07,000
He could make it awfully difficult
for you to spend time with me.

625
00:40:07,035 --> 00:40:08,312
Well--

626
00:40:08,335 --> 00:40:12,327
Who says he has to know
how I spend my free time?

627
00:40:24,835 --> 00:40:28,200
I'm having trouble 
with a family across the street.

628
00:40:28,235 --> 00:40:31,500
I think one of them 
may have set a fire in my house,

629
00:40:31,535 --> 00:40:33,200
and I don't know why, but

630
00:40:33,235 --> 00:40:40,700
I feel like it's got something to do with
my friend who killed herself.

631
00:40:40,735 --> 00:40:44,842
I called the police,
but they didn't take me seriously.

632
00:40:45,735 --> 00:40:49,900
This family has got a secret.
A bad secret.

633
00:40:49,935 --> 00:40:51,200
I think I'm in over my head.

634
00:40:51,235 --> 00:40:57,798
I need you to find out everything about
Paul Young and his family.

635
00:40:58,335 --> 00:41:00,703
Do you think you can help me?

636
00:41:01,835 --> 00:41:07,584
As a matter of fact,
I know I can.

637
00:41:11,635 --> 00:41:15,900
<i>Spring comes every year to Wisteria Lane.

638
00:41:15,935 --> 00:41:21,500
<i>But not everyone remembers to
stop and smell the flowers.

639
00:41:21,535 --> 00:41:27,500
<i>Some are too busy
worrying about the future

640
00:41:27,535 --> 00:41:33,300
<i>or mistakes they've made in the past.

641
00:41:33,335 --> 00:41:37,265
<i>Others are preoccupied with not getting caught,

642
00:41:40,135 --> 00:41:41,798
It's a window!

643
00:41:41,798 --> 00:41:51,800
<i>or thinking of ways
to catch someone else.

644
00:41:51,835 --> 00:41:57,300
<i>Still, there will always be a few
who remember to take a moment

645
00:41:57,335 --> 00:42:00,887
<i>and appreciate what Spring has given them,

646
00:42:03,535 --> 00:42:09,400
<i>just as there will always be those who
prefer to sit in the dark,

647
00:42:09,435 --> 00:42:15,946
<i>brooding over everything they've lost.